OL,3,CRory McIlroy looks for answers on the
OL,4,Crange as Masters lead vanishes
OL,6,FRory McIlroy headed straight to the
OL,7,Fpractice ground range to iron out his
OL,8,Fproblems after surrendering a six-shot
OL,9,Flead to leave the defence of his
OL,10,FMasters title in the balance.
OL,12,FTwenty-four hours earlier, the
OL,13,FNorthern Irishman had looked poised to
OL,14,Fblow the field away after opening up a
OL,15,Fsignificant advantage with the biggest
OL,16,F36-hole lead in the tournament's
OL,17,Fhistory.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/6
